caption: Best urchin(Uni) I have ever had in Boston! So fresh and sweet! Their homemade rolls are delicious, too! I’ll definitely order next time! Salad and Don come with big quantity and good quality. I ordered hot sake for drink. It goes pretty well with the cold winter that day. Overall my friend and I really enjoy the meal!
The food and service were above my expectations. I really liked the vibes of this restaurant. Extraordinary place to take the family out for lunch.
Friendly service, clean, great menu items in Davis Square.
Sushi was amazing, highly recommended!
The food and service were above my expectations. I really loved the environment of this place. Fantastic restaurant to take my family out for lunch.
Excellent food, hand sanitizer at every table, loved the kimchi soba!

I go to this place from time to time! This is the best place to grab a bite.  I visit this spot frequently. The cooking is great, the crew is helpful and the prices are affordable. I like being in this place for a tasty lunch.
Honestly great ^^
I have been vomitting non stop for two hours after having salmon and uni four hours ago it’s the worst pain i have had
I love the Maki combo!
Nice & comfortable atmosphere, friendly staff, good quality is good. However, it was not a true Japanese owned restaurant....🤔
Excellent Sashimi

Every time I drop by Big Softie, this place always has a line waiting outside the door. I've always wanted to try since seeing this hype, being curious about the food that they have, and  I just think their chicken logo is pretty simple and cute.

That is the best sushi restaurant ever! The most tasty and fresh fish! I am extremely happy they are open still during the pandemic and still keep their highest quality! Wish you all the luck to go through this!

Lunch pre-covid  Udon not pictured. Flavor of the broth was good and the noodles were tasty! Coming from someone who doesn't usually like udon or fish based broths it was surprisingly good and not at all fishy!  I really liked the skewers, they tasted fresh and were very flavorful! The jambi has a good marinade and the sausage was very juicy. The dumplings had a great crispy fried skin and the filling was juicy! The meat looked cute on the skewers but it was much easier to eat after taking them off the stick.  Service was also great and they gave us enough time to look over the menu as we waited for the rest of our party. Food all came at around the same time despite ordering different foods and it was all hot and fresh.
The food is delicious and our waitress was super friendly and nice.
Great outdoor seating and Fresh Tasty Sashimi
Really delicious food and well mixed drinks! I would definitely recommend this if you're in the mood for some soba!

Sushi was decent for the price, it came slow, but the service was awful. The waitress never filled our empty water glasses, had a terrible attitude, and charged us for a spicy mayo side without letting us know about the upcharge (we would have gotten it anyway). She often rolled her eyes or said things in a rude tone. I've come here before, and never noticed the poor service, so it was a shock to me and my friends. I wouldn't choose this restaurant again.
Tried this spot already with a friend and I am addicted since then. I enjoy the fantastic atmosphere and delicious dishes and drinks. Keep it up.
It is our second time here. The food is awesome. Will definitely recommend to people.
Hot duck soba is definitely 👎
Excellent outside seating and attentive wait staff pairs well with the delicious food and crisp sake.

Excited to see that they are open during covid. Outdoor seating only, so very limited. I recommend making a reservation. Also the food menu is limited. Ask ahead.  But everything was delicious as always!! Especially the Dragonball! Which is what we come for every time. 😌

Got their cold tempura soba on a hot summer night and ate outdoors (due to the pandemic). Super nice space outside, and a decent number of tables spaced apart. Staff was taking safety precautions seriously. Food was delicious! Their tempura was extra tasty and crispy compared to other places in the area and the noodles had a great springy texture! Huge portion and good variety of tempura (incl a piece of lotus root yum). I would definitely go back and get the same thing again as we as try other things on the menu.

Always a solid choice for sushi and other Japanese delights.Becoming one of my go to choices.Fish is consistently fresh, also interesting combos and appetizers.Great location in Davis Square.Recent visit with comfortable outdoor seating. Try the Dragonball avocado,sushi grade tuna dish!
Wonderful food and service

I had the Million Dollar roll and the New Wave roll. Both were fantastic - fresh ingredients, generous portions of fillings and toppings (Not just big pieces of rice). The service was quick and friendly. Highly recommend
Went for their lunch menu and got the kaisen don with hot homemade soda noodles. Everything was so fresh and delicious. I've also been here for dinner, great experience every time.

We enjoy eating out. Last night we  found this fine restaurant which friends recommended to us. We passed a lovely experience there with superb food and  an experienced team and a great cook. We  added this fine restaurant in our list  and we will surely return very soon.  Highly recommended.
Really goood
Great place for lunch. The price for lunch is fair and taste good. Recommended!
(Translated by Google) Beds  (Original) Lits

Very good food, at very reasonable prices. Very good menu variety of selections.  The restaurant was clean, comfortable and with appropriate background music. Service was prompt and waitress was helpful in discussing selections. The warm soba soup with tempura was very good, rich and flavorful and the  soba noodles were perfectly prepared.

So good. I went for lunch. Got grilled chicken rice and hot soba. Omg I’ve had noodles this soft. Impressive! Grilled chicken is very flavorful. Love the scallion too. Also got Sapporo light for 5$ I like it!
Very disappointed at the hot foods, all premade and reheat to plate. Uni Soba is really good tho!

My first impression is that it's another Japanese Izakaya ran by Chinese, but their offerings are actually very decent. The decor is nice, sushi and apps are both fine, the robata glaze is really good, but the soba is not so great to be the accent in the menu, it's difficult to taste the aroma of buckwheat in the noodle.

Great food. Their appetizers are amazing especially the Scallop Hokkaiyaki. I got the sashimi lunch and the quality of the fish was great. Great portions as well. I love all the wood tables. It's a great place for lunch and dinner
The best sushi in Boston! Nice place and service.
Great soba. A new years tradition!
Okay food but don't expect to have thoughtful or well coordinated service.

This was our first time here. Had the takoyaki, soft shell crab, pork and kimchi soba, veggie roll, and spicy tuna roll. The food was all delicious, well-spiced, and fresh. The broth on the soba noodles was great. My husband and I will definitely be coming back again many times!

My favorite Japanese restaurant in the area. The food is fresh and clearly high quality with options for any eater. The sushi is excellent as is their house made sake. I have come here for multiple occasions, as the place is spacious, inviting, and fun.
Loved their tempura soba
Great and fresh. Had a mixture of sushi and maki roles, all very tasty.
Decor was nice. Got the hot sabo that I felt was a little too mild in flavor; friendly staff

Yummy homemade soba noodle soup along with a bowl of tasty sushi on rice for a lunch special. Delicious, refreshing, and just the right amount of food. The flavors were clean and healthy, and the decor of the restaurant made the experience of the meal that much more elegant and comforting. Beautifully lit floating shelves behind the sushi counters, a wonderfully large wall mural of stylized waves, and a spacious dining room created a zen ambience perfect for intimate conversations.

One of my favorite places to eat Japanese food! My go-to is usually the pork kimchi soba but tonight I got the hot Kitsune soba and split the sushi appetizer with my partner. It was exactly what I needed.
Amazing variety. A great place to bring people with different dietary restrictions.
Drinks are very good here! Recommend the plum whine if you like sour drinks!
The food was really good!
A little pricey but great service and creative dishes that had solid flavor
Great sushi and soba, nice atmosphere

Food was pretty good. My Saporro tasted like a room temperature bud light. I asked for a cold glass, she told me they didnt have them. The staff is mediocre at best. Our waitress in particular was subpar. Oh yea, I forgot to mention that the hostess decided to cut my wife off mid sentence to inform us that people were ahead of us, when all she was doing was asking to sit in a corner booth table that was vacant. Prices are alright...
Fantastic izakaya!
Amazing sushi but service can be a little slow. Overall a great place for dinner or date.
Food and drink are amazing, soba to sushi, sake to whiskey everything is top notch! I go for the Uni Soba or the Millionaire roll and either a Sapporo or a minty mezcal
Enjoyed it.
The food is awesome! Authentic Japanese taste and not expensive. I love the ige yaki, tempula soba, and yakiniku so much!

Food is good but not impressive. Family-style, love it. A bit under-staffed, though.
(Translated by Google) Stay tuned.  (Original) sugIdama.

Sugidama was absolutely delicious! Prior to today, the best tempura I’d ever had was over in Japan, but Sugimara was good enough to surpass it! A high bar! Wonderful, friendly and inclusive staff too—absolutely give this place a shot

Unless you are going off hours, strongly suggest you make reservation. Love uni ikura soba - it is delicious! After eating soba, they also offer free soba soup, very nice touch. Nice casual vibe, great for gathering or just simple indulgence on some good food.

I really enjoyed Sugidama the other day. I went there for lunch and was very satisfied. I got some of their daily specials and was impressed. Their specials are creative and very good. I will return soon.
Delicious sushi and other dishes
Amazing soba and the appetizers are also pretty good.

To me, Sugidama is the crown jewel of the Davis dining scene. The noodles are excellent, as have been all the starters and sides I've tried.  The soba here is thicker and has less buckwheat than most store bought soba. Made in-house, it's chewy and lively. Topped with vegetables and dipped in soy sauce and wasabi, it's refreshing on a hot summer day.  Sugidama also makes their own tofu. Topped with katsuobushi, nori, and scallions or fried and dipped in soy sauce, it's ridiculously silky, smooth, and beany.  Tempura here has nice crisp batter over vegetables or plump juicy shrimp.  The specials board always advertises a mango cake, but they've been out of it both times I've asked.
Excellent restaurant! Great cocktail menu and very well prepared food. We loved everything we ordered

(Translated by Google) The modern store was clean and very good. Soba is also here in the US, and this is absolutely ant! is. The last time Soba-yu came out, I was happy because I didn't expect it. Both sashimi and skewers were delicious! Boston has a lot of rough and miscellaneous restaurants, but I think it's nice when it's small and it's so casual for a date or work end. There is no dress code ☺️ You can dine calmly. The seasoning was relatively delicate and light. I'm glad Because it ’s so salty wherever you go. (Translated by Google) Super sashimi ... fresh fish ... chicken yakitoris ... Only the welcome is disappointing.  (Original) Super sashimis... poissons frais... yakitoris de poulet...Seul l accueil est décevant.

Good but not stellar. Enjoyed a satisfying bowl of soba, and decent quality sashimi. This is the kind of restaurant I would go to if I was hungry and happened to be nearby, but not a food destination. Soba noodles had a good bite to it but the dashi stock seemed pretty much like what you can buy in bottles.
I haven't had anything that I didn't like here. There sushi and grilled skewers are delicious. Bento box set are flavorful and comes with complete set. Service and decor are on point.
All their recommendations were great.
Lovely dishes, good taste, wonderful furniture and friendly people.
Great food in casual venue. Everything we had was well prepared.

Love the atmosphere and the decor here! It is matched with their excellent service and great food! Everything I had there was so delicious and I am looking forward to coming back with my other friends to enjoy the food!
Best place in Davis for sushi

Rating 5 stars because the food was that good! Don't go if you're in any kind of rush, however. We spent well over an hour here for appetizers and dinner. Everything was incredibly fresh and flavorful. Delicious!!
Authentic izakaya menu in a casual no-frills setting.
Love the food.  Friendly staff

We tried this restaurant for the first time today and loved it. Love the decor. The food is awesome. We got the sushi and the noodles and a box with a top on it that had chicken and rice in it. Triple yum!
Every meal has been delicious

Had the Uni Soba. Uni didn't taste very fresh. Cold soba was good. The grilled squid was good but smaller than I thought it would be. The caterpillar roll had small amount of unagi so you could barely taste it through the avocado and cucumber. Otherwise, average Japanese sushi and soba place.
(Translated by Google) A Japanese-style izakaya! Water is free.  (Original) 日本風のよい居酒屋！お水がフリーです。
Loved this place! Tempura soba was amazing. Will def go back for more soba😋
This place is located in the heart of Davis sq and is next to a public parking lot. The food is great, in particular the Soba noodles. The sushi has always been good as well.
Very nice place, good food choices and good service.

Place was great and really reminded me of my time in Japan.  The cold soba is great to try during summer as it refreshes you (tip: pour the broth into the bowl and mix a bit of wasabi in it, then dip the noodles then afterwards, drink the broth). At the very least, you can say you tried it!  Another fun thing to do is to just get a bunch of yakitori (Japanese bbq skewers), you really can't go wrong with that.  Service was fast, I got my soba within ten minutes of me ordering it, on a busy Saturday night nonetheless!
The service and food have greatly improved and the soba has a great texture.  Stay away from the fried food as it still tends to be a little oily.
The udon was pretty good, but just not very inspiring. The service was on the slow side.
This is a solid go-to for sushi in Davis Square. Professional and friendly staff, an abbreviated menu done well, inviting atmosphere that can get noisy at rush periods. Food is consistently good.
Yummy salmon bowl and miso soup, cool communal seating. Very casual vibe.
Café sushi on a budget.
Incredible food

(Translated by Google) There is a limit, but the style is quite similar to a pub. I think that you will be pleased if you invite non-Japanese people. You should make a reservation at night. For groups, up to 8 people would be better.  (Original) 限界はありますが、居酒屋にかなり近いスタイルになっています。日本人以外の方を招待すると喜ばれると思います。夜は予約した方が良いです。グループの場合は8名前後までが良いでしょう。

Super charming and cute little soba restaurant that makes great Soba in house. Their lunch set menu is of great value plus the quality of food is superb. Great staff and service, always refilling my water without asking, always greeted when entering and leaving the restaurant, and food came out quick. Perfect sized portions where I didn’t feel bad paying the price for. Overall, had a pleasant experience.
Kalbi yakitori was the best for me
The sushi rolls and yakitori here are so good! My go-to Japanese restaurant in the neighborhood.
Excellent Soba bowl
Unassuming location with fantastic food and service! Large menu with tons of standard and unique offerings.
Definitely the best option for sushi in Davis Sq.
The yakitori is very flavorful. The pork Kim chi done is delicious.
My yakitoridon was pretty good but a bit expensive for chicken over rice
Incredibly slow service, although the food is pretty good. It's a lot more expensive than similar local places though
Very good, tempura not too oily, broth not too salty. Soba noodles average. Custard preparation very good, seafood in custard tasted fresh. Fried tofu preparation average. Definitely would go back.
Great soba on a cold day!
This is definitely the best Sushi I've had in Boston.
Worth it. Never had soba noodles til now and I'm not disappointed.
One of the rare soba places in America. Uni soba is great. Sushi seems standard.
Delicious food! They serve soba and small tapas-type plates. We got a mix of both which was perfect. My favorite small plate was the enoki mushroom!
If you haven't tried, you're missing out.
Fantastic food and a great green tea cake for dessert
Excellent food. Had sake don.

Really good selection of hot or cold soba. I had the sukiyaki soba which was fairly good with a lot of soba noodles. Also tried the yakitori pork which was really smokey and flavorful. Service was very quick and I was there around mid day. Highly recommend trying this place out.

The food is very expensive for the amount you get, and there aren't many good vegetarian options. I ordered the edamame for an appetizer and a kitsune soba for an entrée. They were both good, but I think the soba was kind of boring because of the texture. I'm sure it would be good for someone that enjoys the texture of noodles in soup though. The fried tofu was oddly sweet, and the noodles were a little too soft for my liking. On the other hand, I've had some of their vegetarian sushi and deserts, and I'd definitely recommend those if you're not on a budget. The service was also excellent.
Fantastic sushi
Excellent prices excellent service excellent food. Would absolutely return.
Portions are hearty except for the cod dish. Can be a hit or miss depending on the dishes u ordered.
Lots of seating available so this place is cozy and very clean atmosphere. The soba and sushi are delicious here. Nicely hidden in Davis square. The price is reasonable as well.
One of my fave Boston restaurants. All the soba dishes are delicious, but my fave is the sukiyaki. The staff is wonderful.

Got here in a cold evening. Ordered Lobster Okinomiyaki, Chu Toro and Amaebi sushi, and some hot and cold soba noodles. The Okinomiyaki was tasty, the sushi were fresh and the medium-fat tuna was on point! Soba was great too, perfect texture and taste. Love this, will be back for more.

The best Izakaya I've tried so far in Boston. The food is amazing, but the service was a bit lackluster. Ordered 4 appetizers and 2 entrees. The hotate hokkaiyaki was really good and one of the better ones I've had in Boston. Kalbi was okay, but I feel like some of the other Korean restaurants does it better. Steamed Egg Chawanmushi is good, but I wish they didn't put chicken in it. I just came back from Japan and never have I seen chicken in a Chawanmushi. Grilled octopus is delicious, but wish it came with a shoyu sauce instead of mayo.  The two entrees we got was the cold duck soba with hot dipping sauce and Ebi Kage. Ebi Kage was delicious and the soup was just how we remembered it in Japan. The cold duck soba though...it took almost 45 minutes to come out. My girlfriend finished her entree and still had to wait for mine to come out! I believe the waitress forgot since she came back halfway through the service and asked if I had the hot duck soba. No apologies or anything. Regardless, I think they rushed in prepping my soba because it was pretty wet and the soup did not stick on like how it's supposed to.  Sooooo, main point is the food was great and definitely deserves 4 stars. The service was abhor as I had to wait extremely long for my entree. If the restaurant was busy, I would understand...but it was not. I will try Sugidama again and will update my review if needed.
Absolutely incredible soba.  Worth the trek to Davis Square.
We had a very nice lunch. The staff was friendly and helpful. The service was quick and efficient.
In the middle of a quiet place clean and new environment, fresh and beautiful food.  Took a lunch break here, both my soul and stomach are calmed and relaxed
Came here to get some take out lunch.  The place looked busy, but it didn’t take too long to receive my food.  My unagi bowel has soup came with it.  Both were delicious.

We went here for yakitori and were not disappointed.  We ordered an assortment of beef, chicken, seafood and vegetable skewers while sitting at the bar.  Coupled with a couple of big Sapporo and finished with cold soba, it was great.  The only complaint we had was that the agedashi tofu must have been fried in a strange way that produced a skin that would rather stay together than be split in to bites.

Great Japanese soba noodle place. We ordered about 5 different appetizers and all were delicious. Loved the fried chicken one. I just wished there were more than 4 pieces. The lobster okonomiyaki was too doughy. It doesn't taste like your traditional okonomiyaki and was a bit small. It could also use some more lobster.  I had the cold uni soba noodle as an entree and was not disappointed. There was a good ratio of soba, uni, and ikura.  Staff was friendly and on point with the water refills. 👍

Worst customer service experience we have ever had. Waited closed to an hour for a party of four and a baby because some questionable and poor table managing decision by the staff. Once we ordered the food, everything came out fast except for 2 order of hot soba noodle. We finished all the food on the table (took approximately 30 mins) and the soba didn't come out until 25 mins later and everyone appetite is already gone. While we were dining, not a single cup of water was refilled. When the bill come, they automatically added 18% tips on top of the total, something they do not deserve for the service they provided.
Great food. Really liked the uni shots specials and the skewers!
Fresh Soba noodles! The menu was extensive, but definitely get some of those noodles. Excellent service, and they even give you some warm broth after to turn your dipping sauce into a soup.
Delicious Japanese fare, a great place for dinner out with friends. Great vegan options, got the bean curd hot soba and the Pickle Me roll. Lychee Blast is a sweet mixed drink, great meal
I strongly recommend the soba here. The noodles here are firm and fun to bite. The yakitori tasted good too, but the portions didn't really feel like a good value.
Excellent, always.
Nice atmosphere, very tasty noodles and great looking dishes. Pretty slow service with dishes arriving for the people in the same party 20 minutes apart.

The food here was great and it's really reasonably priced imo! The waitress overheard me talking to my friend about their birthday and brought us free cake and ice cream without us asking! I'd absolutely come back here or recommend it to anyone looking for some good Japanese food in Davis.

This is a gem of a restaurant hiding just off Davis Sq. The interior is sleek and modern. It was appetizer day for me and first to arrive was the Kurobuta Sausage. It was OK but could have been any sausage. Next was the excellent Pork Belly skewer (Negi Pon). This was followed by the dish of the day, Scallop Hokkaiyaki that was just phenomenal. Hot, spicy, creamy and really tasty. I wasn't too impressed by the Lobster Okonomiyaki even if it had real lobster in the lobster salad. The pancake lacked texture and seasoning.
Uni soba is a must. Other small dishes are pretty authentic and taste great. Service is sometimes not attentive.

A unique selection of food and drinks that challenged me to go beyond plain old ramen or sushi. I got the cold soba noodles with veggie tempura and it was DELICIOUS! My boyfriend ordered the eel and we split a carafe of sake. There was a pretty big line— get there early! However, the person taking names down was kind enough to put my party above another group that cut in front of us on the way through the door.
Good food. The avacado salad was sooo good. Okay service. Terrible mai tai.

Friendly servers and owners, good proper Japanese style food. Their specialty is their soba noodles and their grilled foods. However their sushi are proper and of great quality. While they are not the most affordable eats, they are well worth their cost.

A wide range- perhaps too wide- of Japanese cuisine, ranging from yakitori to soba to sushi and tempura.  My tempura soba came with a good portion of tempura but was lacking on the soba.  Yakitori in general was of acceptable standard- you can’t go wrong with the beef enoki and the honey pork sausage was surprisingly tasty but the Kalbi was exceedingly fatty.  Friendly service.

This restaurant has a cool, spacious interior with friendly staff and very solid-tasting food. We came here right at 5pm on a Saturday and while it wasn't crowded when we first sat down, it was pretty much filled up by the time we left. We started with the chawanmushi hot egg custard and the yellowtail collar -- both were tasty with very fresh ingredients, the former was perhaps just a touch undersalted but the latter was really crispy and well cut to maximize enjoyment of the fish. Then, we each got cold soba -- my partner got the most basic soba with nori and I got the mountain veggies soba. Both were good, with nice, springy noodles.  Our bill came out to be $53. The food was generally solid although I can't say it blew my mind -- I'll concede this may be because I don't know my sobas too well. Only complaint was we were seated right beneath an a/c vent, which made eating (cold!) noodles a little chilly.
Good service. Food is ok.
Very good soba! Really 4.5 stars.
Great soba

Can’t believe how many times I have been here... so I got a bunch of pictures. The fried octopus and tempura shrimp are my must order. Try them if you like fries. Uni soba is so sweet and fresh so if sugidama has uni on hand plz try it! You won’t regret hh!
Great fresh food, and good atmosphere.
Excellent food and service, in a beautiful and calm space in Davis Sq.
Great hot soba! Green tea cheesecake was good too. Nothing bad on the menu, friendly staff.
The food is really good and the fish is really fresh!

Came with a friend who was really craving soba. Got the kitsune hot soba, which came with scallions, 4 slices of fried tofu, and 2 thin slices of fish ball (no other toppings). I was expecting it to be vegetarian since the fish wasn't mentioned in the menu (it does say this dish can be made vegan though). I paid $15+ for this including tax and tip, and was still hungry. My friend paid $3-4 more for a seafood soba, and seemed to get his money's worth. The setting is clean and service is efficient. Would just not recommend for vegetarians.
Extremely delicious, quick service, good vibes! I got the cold soba with pork kimchi broth
Love this place, great good and sharp environment

What fun place for sake and snacks! Don't come hungry - it'll be $$$. We came here full but we wanted to try the uni soba and their grilled skewers. Uni in soba is delicious but prob can be hit or miss on freshness depending on day you come, though the soba itself was underwhelmingfire like spaghetti with a hint of soba, which is no no in Japan for real soba-too much wheat flour. The whole squid skewers was a surprise find.... Ordered 3 rounds of it. They have a sweet Japanese beer that's delicious to go with that squid. Would go back to hang out .
Nice relaxed atmosphere. Waitress was kind. Food was delicious. Prices are up there in terms of the portions you get, but I think it was worth it.
Great sushi and nice environment. Attentive wait staff.
Surprisingly delicious menu. Want to come back for more to try the rest of the menu.
Always love this place for their famous hot and cold soba. Sushi is also good. Don't forget their green tea shortcake.

I adore SS&I. The atmosphere is great for a casual lunch, a romantic meal, or meeting with friends or family. I've been here several times and I've never had a bad or even subpar experience with the staff or the food. I suggest getting the gyoza steamed (pork dumplings) and any of the maki rolls. I'm a big fan of the torch rolls under the house special maki, and everything that I've had under the makimono heading (by now, more than half of the rolls,) so I can happily endorse this restaurant and their fine sushi. In my opinion the cherry on top of this fine establishment is that the staff is always friendly and offers quick service. Highly rated because I highly recommend them.

Great option for really good (homemade!) soba and other Japanese food that's much better than what you typically find. Their lunch special are a great deal for a lot of food. I'm only taking off one star because they can be a little slow so you need a flexible lunch break!
Best sushi in the area by far.
Beautiful decor and very tasty sushi!
Fresh seafood which is what you want. Good mix of items on the menu. Popular spot so make sure to have reservations.
Try the Sushi Boat for a enjoyable experience!
This is my favorite sushi place in the city! The menu is a little pedestrian, but the food is excellent and reasonably priced, the service is good, and I love the atmosphere.
Uni soba here is amazing!  A pile of fresh uni on top of delicious soba is hard to find even in Tokyo.
Really good soba and izakaya. The uni soba is delicious and a great value at $16. You get a significant pile of uni!
One of the most legit Japanese restaurants in Somerville/Boston
Decent sushi, nice clean space
Nice place with good food and sake.  The green tea desert was delicious!
This place is really good.  I dined with my family so we shared all the dishes.  Every one was excellent.  I especially liked the scallop carpacio

Very good food and is more authentic than other Japanese restaurants in the area. Definitely need to go back and try more of their menu. The fish tasted fresh and all the dishes we ordered were very tasty.
It's ok. Nothing special.
Good sushi and amazing uni soba!
Just okay. Tempura oil needed to be changed- greasy, not light.
Always a good experience. Only not pick this time was the soba noodles had a lot of small pieces.
Great quality food. Great drinks too.

Great sushi and soba noodles.  We ordered a duck soba and pork soba, which were both delicious. The duck was cooked perfectly and was very flavorful. Service was friendly and very quick.  They also have a decent dessert selection (mochi ice cream, regular ice cream, sponge cakes, cheesecake, crepes and green tea cakes).
Quaint and unique, with really good specials.
Sushi was delicious! Soba good too. Great drinks selection. Fun for an outing with a group of friends.

This is my favorite sushi place in Somerville. Their decor is calm Japanese simplicity and the food is exceptional. I particularly love the Saki Don (salmon sashimi and salmon roe over sushi rice) and the traditional soba with pork and poached egg. But my absolute favorite is the lunch special where you can get a combo with smaller portions with both! All of the yakitori I've tried so far had been delicious too.
Great location, good food. I have had mixed experience with staff. The Japanese community in Boston regularly describes this restaurant as reasonably close to the real thing.
A real Japanese joint with a friendly and welcoming staff!
Not authentic Japanese as it's run entirely by Chinese people. Food is ok, though very expensive with tiny portions.

We went there around noon time on Thursday without reservation. Managed to get seats without waiting. Ordered kaisen don, yakitori don and ika yaki. Food is okay. Portion is small for lunch. The ika yaki did not come. Also waited for quite a while before we could get the waitress and ask for bill. We realized the staff forgot to put in the order when we received the bill. Felt a bit disappointed and only half full. I think this place is understaffed.
Great lunch spot
Really fantastic Japanese food. Excellent atmosphere. The Sashimi Soba was especially delicious.

Soup was underwhelming and tempura was a little too much dough imo.

Craving uni (sea urchin)? Order the handmade uni soba. A great izakaya to visit in the Cambridge area. Take the Red line to Davis Square and it's a 5 min walk from there.  Follow my Instagram @andrewngui to discover more food recommendations!
Great atmosphere- delicious food! Cocktails are also great
Stuff was nice and friendly and the food was good, I am glad we went.
Food was beautifully presented, fresh, and delicious. Prices were reasonable and service was fast.
My favorite Japanese restaurant,  I could eat there twice a month. The service is good too.

Excellent food and great service. A little pricey, hence the 4 stars, but somewhat expected of Davis Square. We went here the first week they opened and love going back. Very authentic foods served how they should be.
